<div id="review_21645305" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/21645305" />
    <a title="Cheryl" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/737672-cheryl"><img alt="Cheryl" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1219862680p2/737672.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/21645305?book_show_action=true">May 05, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cheryl" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cheryl" href="/user/show/737672-cheryl">Cheryl</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/737672-cheryl?shelf=brazilian">brazilian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer21645305" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer452133299623969756">This is a beautifully and imaginatively written story about an everyday woman who has to come to terms with different facets of her own personality and what that means about the men she falls in love with and how she loves them in return. She has trouble reconciling her emotions, which seem so contrary to her: her passionate, steamy, violent, up-and-down young romance with her first husband, who dies an untimely death, and her sedate, kind, gentle, secure, and structured but still caring and ten</span>
  <span id="freeText452133299623969756" style="display:none">This is a beautifully and imaginatively written story about an everyday woman who has to come to terms with different facets of her own personality and what that means about the men she falls in love with and how she loves them in return. She has trouble reconciling her emotions, which seem so contrary to her: her passionate, steamy, violent, up-and-down young romance with her first husband, who dies an untimely death, and her sedate, kind, gentle, secure, and structured but still caring and tender relationship with her second husband, who is everything the first was not. I'm very surprised at how well a man is able to tap into the raw emotions and desires of a female character, but Jorge Amado can be an honorary woman in my book! The spiritual notes from the voodoo or candomble world and from the spirits themselves might be a little much for a contemporary secular reader to swallow, but if you can open your mind and get past that, it's well worth it. </span>
  <a data-text-id="452133299623969756" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


